        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(google): stop appending -preview to gemini-3.1-flash-lite",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nGoogle graduated `gemini-3.1-flash-lite` to GA on 2026-05-07 and deprecated the `-preview` endpoint (shutdown 2026-05-25). OpenClaw's normalizer unconditionally appends `-preview` to every `gemini-3.1-flash-lite` reference, sending requests to a deprecated endpoint and ignoring the user's explicit model choice.\n\nThis reverses the mapping direction: the non-preview GA name is now canonical, and old `-preview` references normalize to the GA id.\n\nCloses #86151\n\n## Changes\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `extensions/google/model-id.ts` | Reverse normalizer: `flash-lite-preview` maps to `flash-lite` (was the opposite) |\n| `extensions/google/openclaw.plugin.json` | Reverse alias key/value in all three provider sections |\n| `src/plugin-sdk/provider-model-id-normalize.ts` | Same reversal in the shared SDK normalizer |\n| `src/config/defaults.ts` | `gemini-flash-lite` alias now points to GA id |\n\n## Verification\n\n```\nBehavior addressed: gemini-3.1-flash-lite no longer gets -preview appended\nReal environment tested: macOS 15.5, Node 24, pnpm test\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n  pnpm test extensions/google/model-id.test.ts\n  pnpm test src/plugin-sdk/provider-model-id-normalize.test.ts\n  pnpm test src/config/model-alias-defaults.test.ts\n  pnpm test src/agents/model-selection.test.ts\n  pnpm test src/plugins/provider-runtime.test.ts\n  pnpm test src/media-understanding/image.test.ts\nEvidence after fix:\n  extensions/google/model-id.test.ts — 11 passed\n  provider-model-id-normalize.test.ts — 13 passed (new GA+preview coverage)\n  model-alias-defaults.test.ts — 5 passed\n  model-selection.test.ts — 72 passed\n  provider-runtime.test.ts — 51 passed\n  image.test.ts — 8 passed\nObserved result after fix:\n  normalizeGoogleModelId('gemini-3.1-flash-lite') === 'gemini-3.1-flash-lite' (unchanged, GA)\n  normalizeGoogleModelId('gemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview') === 'gemini-3.1-flash-lite' (maps to GA)\nWhat was not tested: live Google API call (no credentials in test env)\n```\n",
        "branch": "fix/gemini-flash-lite-ga",
